         <abstract>
            <p>This paper offers a general expansion formula for oscillatory integrals of the form $\int^1_0x^{-\alpha}f(x, \{Nx\})dx$ in which $N$ is a large parameter, $\{Nx\}$ denotes the fractional part of $Nx$, and $\alpha$ is a fixed real number in $0 &lt; \alpha &lt; 1$. Our formula is expressed in terms of some ordinary integrals with integrands containing periodic Bernoulli functions and the generalized Riemann zeta function.</p>
          </abstract>
